Senator Abdullahi Adamu has officially assumed office as the National Chairman of the All Progressives Congress (APC) at the party’s National Secretariat in Abuja. Adamu arrived at the Buhari House by 11 am on Wednesday alongside other members of the National Working Committee (NWC) as a crowd of supporters cheered them on as they settled for the business of the day. Daily Independent had reported that Adamu, former Governor of Nasarawa State emerged as the winner of the party national chairman during the APC National Convention held on Saturday, March 26, in Abuja. This is his first appearance at the party’s headquarters since his election.